x4freetext: Each target was mounted in an evacuated 13 inch
diameter scattering chamber, with Mylar entrance and
extracted from the cyclotron, giving a beam intensity
with a telescope, consisting of two plastic
scintillators and a Harshaw 3 X 3 inch sodium iodide
The resolution was 1.35 MeV FWHM at 160 MeV. The
angular resolution of the counter system was +/- 0.5
degrees. The counter telescope was mounted on a 5 feet
arm, which could be rotated on a track about the
scattering chamber. The angle could be determined to
within 0.1 degrees. The zero direction was determined
to within +/- 0.1 degrees by measuring on both sides.
A nonsaturating He ionization chamber was used
to monitor the incident proton beam. This chamber was
